==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*arga-'', from Indo-European ''*ergh-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[arg]], Old High German [[arg]] (German, Dutch [[arg]]), Old Norse [[argr]] (Swedish, Danish [[arg]]).

